The article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring April 2015 as National Donate Life Month. The proclamation highlights the critical shortage of organ donors in the United States, with over 123,000 Americans in need of a life-saving organ transplant. It emphasizes the importance of becoming an organ, eye, and tissue donor, as one person's decision can save up to eight lives and enhance many more. The proclamation encourages individuals of all ages and backgrounds to consider becoming a donor and to discuss this choice with friends and family. It calls upon various groups, including health care professionals, volunteers, educators, and government agencies, to work together to increase the number of donors in the country. The proclamation concludes by urging solidarity and efforts to save and improve the lives of Americans in need.